{"lemma":"غَلَقَ","slug":"غَلَقَ","root":"غ.ل.ق","root_slug":"غ-ل-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ل-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":15},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32280"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shut, to close (a door)","examples":[{"text":"Abu al-Aswad al-Du'ali\nوَلَا أَقُولُ لِقِدْرِ ٱلقَوْمِ قَدْ غَلِيَتْ\nوَلَا أَقُولُ لِبَابِ ٱلدَّارِ مَغْلُوقُ\nلَكِنْ أَقُولُ لِبَابِي مُغْلَقٌ وَغَلَتْ\nقِدْرِي وَقَابَلَهَا دَنٌّ وَإِبْرِيقُ\nwalā ʔaqūlu liqidri l-qawmi qad ḡaliyat\nwalā ʔaqūlu libābi d-dāri maḡlūqu\nlakin ʔaqūlu libābī muḡlaqun waḡalat\nqidrī waqābalahā dannun waʔibrīqu","english":"(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to travel far"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become forfeit to the receiver when not redeemed in a stipulated time (of a pledge)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be unransomed or unredeemed"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stick fast (of one's heart, temper, etc.)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become disquieted by grief"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become angry"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have worms in the base of its branches, rendering it unable to produce fruit (of a palm tree)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become galled with galls not to be cured (of a camel's back)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to close in large numbers or thoroughly","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"وَرَاوَدَتْهُ الَّتِي هُوَ فِي بَيْتِهَا عَنْ نَفْسِهِ وَغَلَّقَتِ الأَبْوَابَ وَقَالَتْ هَيْتَ لَكَ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of غَلَقَ (ḡalaqa, “to lock, shut”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"locking, shutting"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of غَلِقَ (ḡaliqa, “to become forfeit when not redeemed in time”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bolt, keyless wooden lock"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"keystone"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ɣa.la.qa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32280","headword_ar":"غَلَقَ","root":"glq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agolaqa","text_ar":"اَغْلَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the latter.       -A2-  Also, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galoqN","text_ar":"غَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galaqa fiY AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"غَلَقَ فِى الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galoqN","text_ar":"غَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went far into the land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, O, K, * TA;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaqa","text_ar":"فَلَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faloqN","text_ar":"فَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn-'Abbád, O, TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiqa","text_ar":"غَلِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a door: see 7. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiqa","text_ar":"غَلِقَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ahonu","text_ar":"الرَّهْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K, &c.,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galaqN","text_ar":"غَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guluwqN","text_ar":"غُلُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, TA,) or both, (Sb, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pledge was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, a rightful possession"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a forfeit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the receiver of it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when not redeemed within the time stipulated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiqa Alr~ahonu fiY","text_ar":"غَلِقَ الرَّهْنُ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadi Almurotahini","text_ar":"يَدِ المُرْتَهِنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sb, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiqa Alr~ahonu","text_ar":"غَلِقَ الرَّهْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the pledge remained in the hand"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possession"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the receiver of it, the pledger being unable to redeem it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA;) accord. to the Bári', it is when a man pledges a commodity and says, “ If I do not pay thee within such a time, the pledge shall be thine for the debt. ” (Msb.) This is forbidden in a trad. (S, Mgh, O, Msb, &c.) It is said in a trad. of the Prophet on this subject,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yagolaqu bimaA","text_ar":"لَا يَغْلَقُ بِمَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi laka gunomuhu wuEalayoka guromuhu","text_ar":"فِيهِ لَكَ غُنْمُهُ وُعَلَيْكَ غُرْمُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It shall not become a forfeit to the receiver with what is involved in it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or, accord. to an explanation of the first clause in the Msb,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it shall not become a rightful possession to the receiver for the debt for which it was pledged:"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to thee shall pertain the regaining of it, and its increase, and growth, and excess in value, if such there be, and upon thee shall be the obligation of the debt belonging to it, and the bearing of any unavoidable damage that it may have sustained"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu gunomuhu waEalayohi","text_ar":"لَهُ غُنْمُهُ وَعَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guromuhu","text_ar":"غُرْمُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., accord. to A 'Obeyd,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the owner)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it shall return, and to him shall pertain its increase"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if there be any"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and if it have become defective,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have perished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unavoidably,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he shall be responsible for it and shall pay the debt to him to whom it is owed without being compensated by"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the remission of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aught of the debt:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laka","text_ar":"لَكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunomuhu waEalayohi guromuhu","text_ar":"غُنْمُهُ وَعَلَيْهِ غُرْمُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the pledger)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall pertain the increase of it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the pledge),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and its growth, and its excess in value,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if it have any,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and upon him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the receiver of it)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be the responsibility"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to make compensation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for it if it perish"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"through his fault, in his possession"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (O. [There are other, somewhat different, readings and explanations of this trad. in the Mgh &c.; but what I have here given, from the O and Msb, appear to me to be the most approvable. See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunomN","text_ar":"غُنْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rhn","text_ar":"رهن"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) Zuheyr says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wafaAraqatoka birahonK laA fakaAka lahu\n                      \n                     \n                        yawoma AlwadaAEi faA^amosaY Alr~ahonu qado galiqaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And she separated herself from thee with a pledge for which there is nothing wherewith it may be redeemed, on the day of valediction, so the pledge has become a forfeit to its receiver"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Mgh, O, TA:) he means that she received his heart as a pledge, and went away with it. (Mgh, TA.) The saying of Ows Ibn-Hajar"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^abuw galaqK fiY layolatayoni muw^aj~ali"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The owner of a pledge that has become a rightful possession"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forfeit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to its receiver, the period for the release of which is two nights:"},{"kind":"text","text":"to this he likens a captivated heart. (TA.) ―         -b3-  One says also, of a slave who has received permission to traffic,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiqato raqabatuhu biAld~ayoni","text_ar":"غَلِقَتْ رَقَبَتُهُ بِالدَّيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqabap","text_ar":"رَقَبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"person"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has become a rightful possession"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a forfeit"},{"kind":"text","text":"to his creditor or creditors]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of debt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"when he is unable to free it. (Mgh.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiqa","text_ar":"غَلِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was unransomed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unredeemed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a captive, and of a criminal. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, stuck fast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA:) thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiqa qalobuhu fiY yadi fulaAnapa","text_ar":"غَلِقَ قَلْبُهُ فِى يَدِ فُلَانَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His heart stuck fast in the possession of such a woman"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"girl"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiHotad~a fagaliqa fiY Hid~atihi","text_ar":"اِحْتَدَّ فَغَلِقَ فِى حِدَّتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became excited by sharpness of temper, and stuck fast in his sharpness of temper"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O. TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiqa","text_ar":"غَلِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said of anything that sticks fast in a thing, and cleaves to it: thus one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiqa fiY","text_ar":"غَلِقَ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaATili","text_ar":"البَاطِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stuck fast in that which was vain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"false"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and the saying of El-Farezdak"},{"kind":"quote","text":"walawo kaAnuwA A^uwliY galaqK sigaAbaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Had they been persons who had stack fast in poverty and hunger, cleaving thereto."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, TA.) ―         -b6-  Also, (Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galaqN","text_ar":"غَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, disquieted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disquieted by grief;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"angry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA.) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excited by sharpness of temper."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamiynu Algalaqi","text_ar":"يَمِينُ الغَلَقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The oath of anger;"},{"kind":"text","text":"said by some of the lawyers to be so called because he who swears it closes thereby against himself a door preventing him from advancing or drawing back. (Msb.) And hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iy~aAka waAlgalaqa","text_ar":"اـِيَّاكَ وَالغَلَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beware thou of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avoid thou, the being disquieted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disquieted by grief"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anger"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or, as some say, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aToliyqaAtu Hat~aY laA yaboqaY minohaA","text_ar":"التَّطْلِيقَاتُ حَتَّى لَا يَبْقَى مِنْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yugolaqu","text_ar":"لَا يُغْلَقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'N","text_ar":"شَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sentences of divorce shall not be closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"concluded, at once,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by one's saying “ Thou art trebly divorced, ”"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that there shall not remain of them aught"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; for one should divorce agreeably with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sun~ap","text_ar":"سُنَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) [or, accord. to the TA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iy~aAka waAlgalaqa","text_ar":"اـِيَّاكَ وَالغَلَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beware thou of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avoid thou, the state of straitness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algalaqu","text_ar":"الغَلَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the being in a state of perdition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contractedness of the mind"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bosom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mbr, JK, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"paucity of patience."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mbr, TA.) ―         -b7-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiqati Aln~axolapu","text_ar":"غَلِقَتِ النَّخْلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O. K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galaqN","text_ar":"غَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) :"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The palm-tree had worms in the bases of its branches and was thereby stopped from bearing fruit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani AlA_ivomaAri","text_ar":"عَنِ الاـِثْمَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ugoliqato","text_ar":"اُغْلِقَتْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b8-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiqa Zahoru","text_ar":"غَلِقَ ظَهْرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaEiyri","text_ar":"البَعِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galaqN","text_ar":"غَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The back of the camel became galled with galls not to be cured;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the whole of his back being seen to be two portions of cicatrized skin, the results of galls that had become in a healing state, and the two sides thereof glistening:"},{"kind":"text","text":"ISh says that in the case of the worst galls of the camel, the furniture, or saddle and saddle-cloth, cannot be [partially] raised from contact with him [so as to be bearable by him]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","IAar","TA","Sb","Mgh","K","Mbr","JK"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}